<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36192b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36192b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36192b"> 192(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bottleholders</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To assist the doubtful Walter in the arduous business of legislation, a board of magistrates was appointed, which presided immediately over the police. This potent body consisted of a schout or bailiff &hellip;, five burgermeesters &hellip;, and five <mark>schepens</mark>, who officiated as scrubs, subdevils, or <mark>bottle-holders</mark> to the burghermeesters, in the same manner as do assistant aldermen to their principals at the present day. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 84</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
